-- Food retailer Smart & Final's shares rise about 11.6 pct in debut
-- By Avik Das in Bangalore
-- Wed Sep 24, 2014 09:43AM EDT
-- None



Sept 24 (Reuters) - Shares of Smart & Final Stores Inc <SFS.N> rose about 11.6 percent in their debut, valuing the century-old food retailer at $951.44 million.

Smart & Final raised about $161.4 million, after its offering was priced at $12 per share, the low-end of its expected price range of $12-$14. The company, backed by private equity firm Ares Management LP <ARES.N>, is selling all the 13.45 million shares in the offering. Smart & Final's shares opened at $13.10 and touched a high of $13.39.